Interface GraphPathSegment

public interface GraphPathSegment

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type
    Method
    Description
    String
    getId()
    Returns the id associated with this segment, or null if this segment is a direct child property that has no associated id

    Returns the name of the corresponding JSON property for this segment.

  • Method Details

    • isRoot

      boolean isRoot()
      Returns true if this represents the root path segment, false otherwise

    • isArray

      boolean isArray()
      Returns true if the corresponding JSON property is an array, false otherwise. Array properties will always have an associated id.

    • isMap

      boolean isMap()
      Returns true if the corresponding JSON property is an object where that object's properties correspond to ids. Map properties will always have an associated id. Note that a property that is not the root, and which is not an array or map, is just a "normal" JSON property that maps to a direct sub-object with no id.

    • getParent

      GraphPathSegment getParent()
      Returns the parent GraphPathSegment, or null if this path segment is the root

    • getJsonPropertyName

      String getJsonPropertyName()
      Returns the name of the corresponding JSON property for this segment.

    • getId

      String getId()
      Returns the id associated with this segment, or null if this segment is a direct child property that has no associated id
